<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1897-11-13T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1897-11-13T00:00:00-05:00" n="53" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d53">
                        <head><hi rend="italic">Mr. <persName type="from">Sherman</persName> to Mr.
                                    <persName type="to">Mendonça</persName>.</hi></head>
                        <opener><dateline rendition="#right"><placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">Department of State</hi>,<lb/><hi rend="italic">Washington</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1897-11-13"><hi rend="italic">November 13,
                                    1897</hi></date>.</dateline>
                            <seg rendition="#left">No. 19.]</seg></opener>
                        <p><hi rend="smallcaps">Sir</hi>: It has given me pleasure to receive your
                            note of the 10th instant, reporting the appreciation with which the
                            President and Government of Brazil have received, through our minister
                            at Petropolis, the message of the President of the United States
                            expressing his congratulations at the escape of President Moraes from
                            assassination and his condolence in view of the murder of Marshal Bitten
                            court.</p>
                        <p>Accept, etc.,</p>
                        <closer><signed><hi rend="smallcaps">John Sherman.</hi></signed></closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>